The paper deals with embeddings and approximation of matrix norms, which are fundamental topics in computer science. The focus on data streams and linear sketching models of computation suggests that cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.IT (Information Theory) are likely categories. The use of these embeddings in machine learning and optimization problems suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as another possible category. The study of approximation algorithms and numerical analysis suggests cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as a possible category. Finally, the use of linear maps and matrix multiplication suggests cs.SY (Systems and Control) as a possible category.
